'''Ono Shrine''' (おのじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} in Ono, {{jalink|Ōtsu|Q202907}}, {{jalink|Shiga Prefecture|Q131358}}. It is a {{jalink|Shikinaisha}}. Its former rank was {{jalink|gōsha|Q134917316}}. The {{jalink|enshrined deity|Q11591100}} is {{jalink|Kome-mochi-tsuki-ōomi|Q11604425|Kome-mochi-tsuki-ōomi-no-Mikoto}}, ancestor of the {{jalink|Ono clan|Q11464141}}, and is said to be the ancestral deity of mochi making in Japan. For that reason, the annual Shitogi Festival receives worshipers from confectionery industries across Japan. The shrine crest is Mitsume.

=== History ===
This area is the base of the {{jalink|Ono clan|Q11464141}}. The founding period is unknown, but it was designated a {{jalink|Shikinaisha}} ({{jalink|myōjin taisha|Q9610964}}). In {{jalink|1891|Q7837}} ({{jalink|Meiji|Q3125096}} 24), it was ranked as a {{jalink|gōsha|Q134917316}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* Main deities - {{jalink|Ama-tarashihiko-kuni-oshi-hito-no-Mikoto|Q11443593}}, {{jalink|Tachikara-mochi-tsuki no omi|Q11604425|Kome-mochi-tsuki-ōomi-no-Mikoto}}

