'''Ono Shrine''' (おのじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Ono, {{ill|lt=Ōtsu|Q202907|WD=Q202907|1=Ōtsu}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}. Its former rank was {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}. The {{ill|lt=enshrined deity|Q11591100|WD=Q11591100|1=Saijin}} is {{ill|lt=Kome-mochi-tsuki-ōomi|Q11604425|WD=Q11604425|lt=Kome-mochi-tsuki-ōomi-no-Mikoto|1=Taganetsuki no Ōomi no Mikoto}}, ancestor of the {{ill|lt=Ono clan|Q11464141|WD=Q11464141|1=Ono clan}}, and is said to be the ancestral deity of mochi making in Japan. For that reason, the annual Shitogi Festival receives worshipers from confectionery industries across Japan. The shrine crest is Mitsume.

=== History ===
This area is the base of the {{ill|lt=Ono clan|Q11464141|WD=Q11464141|1=Ono clan}}. The founding period is unknown, but it was designated a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=myōjin taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}). In {{ill|lt=1891|Q7837|WD=Q7837|1=1891}} ({{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 24), it was ranked as a {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* Main deities - {{ill|lt=Ama-tarashihiko-kuni-oshi-hito-no-Mikoto|Q11443593|WD=Q11443593|1=Prince Ametarashihiko}}, {{ill|lt=Tachikara-mochi-tsuki no omi|Q11604425|WD=Q11604425|lt=Kome-mochi-tsuki-ōomi-no-Mikoto|1=Taganetsuki no Ōomi no Mikoto}}

